Class Manager

  • java.lang.Object
    • it.unisa.diem.softwareengineering.assignment2021.Manager

  • public class Manager
extends java.lang.Object
    The Manager of the Complex Calculator, which makes the comunication between the GUI, the Memory and the available operations possible.

      • processInput

        public void processInput(java.lang.String input)
                  throws java.lang.NumberFormatException,
                         NotEnoughOperatorsException,
                         java.lang.ArithmeticException,
                         java.util.NoSuchElementException
        Processes the input submitted by the user and operates on the stack according to the contents of the input, that could be a new number insertion or an operation, then proceeds to update the stack accordingly.
        Parameters:
        input - the String inputted from the user which will be parsed.
        Throws:
        java.lang.NumberFormatException - when the input doesn't correspond neither to an operation, nor to a properly formatted Complex Number.
        NotEnoughOperatorsException - when there aren't enough operands in the memory to process an operation
        java.lang.ArithmeticException - when a arithmetically illegal operation occurs.
        java.util.NoSuchElementException

        public java.lang.String insertPersonalizedOperation(java.lang.String name,
                                                    java.lang.String operations)
                                             throws PersonalizedOperationException
        Inserts a personalized operation into runtime environment, so that it can be later called again.
        Parameters:
        name - the name of the personalized operation
        operations - the list of elementary operations that compose the personalized operation
        Returns:
        the new name of the operation
        Throws:
        PersonalizedOperationException - when a element of operations isn't recognized, naming the operation with a complex number or the name contains a space.
